.TH "update_usable_mem_fdt" 9 "update_usable_mem_fdt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
update_usable_mem_fdt \- Updates kdump kernel's fdt with linux,usable-memory and linux,drconf-usable-memory DT properties as appropriate to restrict its memory usage.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" update_usable_mem_fdt
.BI "(void *fdt "  ","
.BI "struct crash_mem *usable_mem "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fdt" 12
Flattened device tree for the kdump kernel.
.IP "usable_mem" 12
Usable memory ranges for kdump kernel.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, negative errno on error.
